comments: Jordan (NYK) makes marginal contact with Barnes (SAC) that does not affect his ability to control the entry pass.
Jordan (NYK) maintains legal guarding position as body contact is made with Barnes (SAC) during the drive.
Bjelica (SAC) makes incidental "high-five" contact with Thomas (NYK) after the release of his jump shot attempt.
Thomas (NYK) and Barnes (SAC) engage and disengage off-ball without affecting the other's FOM.
Thomas (NYK) makes contact with Fox's (SAC) right wrist, causing his right hand to come off of the ball during his driving shot attempt.
Smith Jr. (NYK) gathers the ball on his left foot and takes two legal steps thereafter.
Hield (SAC) makes marginal contact with Smith Jr.'s (NYK) body during his driving shot attempt.
Bjelica (SAC) slightly extends his hands against Smith Jr.'s (NYK) backside, but the contact is marginal and does not affect his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Barnes (SAC) makes marginal contact with Jenkins (NYK) as he slips the pick.
Jordan (NYK) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Jordan (NYK) establishes himself in a screening position in Barnes' (SAC) defensive path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Barnes (SAC) and Jordan (NYK) engage with each other as they move through the lane but disengage as the shot goes up without affecting the other's ability to retrieve the rebound.
Cauley-Stein (SAC) establishes himself in a screening position in Jenkins' (NYK) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Bjelica (SAC) and Jenkins (NYK) engage and disengage off-ball without affecting the other's FOM.
